### [1 Chronicles Chapter 4](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#001.md)

[1 Chronicles 4:1](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">ch1 4:1</span></span>

The (a) sons of Judah; Pharez, Hezron, and Carmi, and Hur, and Shobal.

\(a\) Meaning, they came from Judah, as nephews and kinsmen: for only
Pharez was his natural son.

[1 Chronicles 4:4](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">ch1 4:4</span></span>

And Penuel the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah. These
\[are\] the sons of Hur, the (b) firstborn of Ephratah, the father of
Bethlehem.

\(b\) The first born of his mother, and not the eldest of his father.

[1 Chronicles 4:9](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">ch1 4:9</span></span>

And Jabez was more honourable than his brethren: and his mother called
his name (c) Jabez, saying, Because I bare him with sorrow.

\(c\) Otherwise called Othniel, ([Jdg
1:13](../../../bib/kjv/jdg001.htm#013).md).

[1 Chronicles 4:10](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">ch1 4:10</span></span>

And Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, Oh that thou wouldest
bless me indeed, and enlarge my coast, and (d) that thine hand might be
with me, and that thou wouldest keep \[me\] from evil, that it may not
grieve me! And God granted him that which he requested.

\(d\) It is to be understood that then he would accomplish his vow which
he made.

[1 Chronicles 4:14](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">ch1 4:14</span></span>

And Meonothai begat Ophrah: and Seraiah begat Joab, the (e) father of
the valley of Charashim; for they were craftsmen.

\(e\) The Lord of the valley where the artificers worked.

[1 Chronicles 4:15](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">ch1 4:15</span></span>

And the sons of Caleb the son of (f) Jephunneh; Iru, Elah, and Naam: and
the sons of Elah, even Kenaz.

\(f\) Called also Esrom.

[1 Chronicles 4:23](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">ch1 4:23</span></span>

These \[were\] the potters, and those that dwelt among plants and
hedges: (g) there they dwelt with the king for his work.

\(g\) They were David's gardeners and served him in his works.

[1 Chronicles 4:24](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">ch1 4:24</span></span>

The sons of Simeon \[were\], Nemuel, and Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, \[and\]
(h) Shaul:

\(h\) His son Obed is omitted here.

[1 Chronicles 4:28](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">ch1 4:28</span></span>

And they dwelt at (i) Beersheba, and Moladah, and Hazarshual,

\(i\) These cities belonged to Judah, ([Jos
19:2](../../../bib/kjv/jos019.htm#002).md), and were given to the tribe of
Simeon.

[1 Chronicles 4:31](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">ch1 4:31</span></span>

And at Bethmarcaboth, and Hazarsusim, and at Bethbirei, and at Shaaraim.
These \[were\] their cities unto the reign of (k) David.

\(k\) Then David restored them to the tribe of Judah.

[1 Chronicles 4:39](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#039.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_039">ch1 4:39</span></span>

And they (l) went to the entrance of Gedor, \[even\] unto the east side
of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks.

\(l\) For the tribe of Simeon was so great in number, that in the time
of Hezekiah they sought new dwellings to Gedor, which is in the tribe of
Dan.

[1 Chronicles 4:43](../../../bib/kjv/ch1004.htm#043.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_043">ch1 4:43</span></span>

And they smote the rest of the Amalekites that were (m) escaped, and
dwelt there unto this day.

\(m\) And were not slain by Saul and David.

